  "body": "Note that this is not a security issue, since `bn256.G1.Add` is only used in `vm.runBn256Add`, and is not used in-place, there. Also, a [fix has been provided upstream](https://github.com/cloudflare/bn256/pull/12), and just hasn't been pulled in. My recommendation to fix this would be to make [these changes](https://github.com/cloudflare/bn256/pull/12/files) to to `go-ethereum`'s `cloudflare/bn256`.\r\n\r\nA failing test is provided below, in the \"Expected Behavior\" section.\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth `version:` `geth version` => `1.15` (master) \r\nOS & Version: Windows/Linux/OSX\r\n```\r\nuname -a\r\nLinux ubuntu-VirtualBox 5.4.0-74-generic #83-Ubuntu SMP Sat May 8 02:35:39 UTC 2021 x86_64 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux\r\n```\r\n\r\nCommit hash : (if `develop`) `28ba686cb`\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nFollowing test of `bn256.G1` addition should pass:\r\n\r\n```golang\r\nfunc TestG2SelfAddition(t *testing.T) {\r\n\ts, _ := rand.Int(rand.Reader, Order)\r\n\tp := new(G2).ScalarBaseMult(s)\r\n\tif _, err := p.Unmarshal(p.Add(p, p).Marshal()); err != nil {\r\n\t\tt.Fatalf(\"p.Add(p, p) ∉ G₂: %v\", err)\r\n\t}\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\n```\r\nubuntu@ubuntu-VirtualBox:~/alien/go-ethereum/crypto/bn256/cloudflare$ go test -run  TestG2SelfAddition\r\n--- FAIL: TestG2SelfAddition (0.00s)\r\n    bn256_test.go:122: p.Add(p, p) ∉ G₂: bn256: coordinate exceeds modulus\r\nFAIL\r\nexit status 1\r\nFAIL\tgithub.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/crypto/bn256/cloudflare\t0.005s\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\n- Add the above test to `crypto/bn256/cloudflare/bn256_test.go` on `master`\r\n- `go test -run  TestG2SelfAddition`\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\nN/A",
